{"title_page": "Technological Educational Institute of Central Greece", "text_new": "{{Infobox university\n|name =Technological Educational Institute <br/>of Central Greece\n|native_name =\u03a4\u03b5\u03c7\u03bd\u03bf\u03bb\u03bf\u03b3\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc \u0395\u03ba\u03c0\u03b1\u03b9\u03b4\u03b5\u03c5\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc \u038a\u03b4\u03c1\u03c5\u03bc\u03b1 <br/>\u03a3\u03c4\u03b5\u03c1\u03b5\u03ac\u03c2 \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1\u03c2\n|former_names =Technological Educational Institute of Lamia <br/>(1994\u20132013)<br/>\nTechnological Educational Institute of Larissa at the <br/>City of Lamia <br/>(1983\u20131994)\n|established =2019 \u2013 Abolished<br>2013 \u2013 Technological Educational Institute <br/>of Central Greece\n\n|type=[[Public university|Public University]]<br/>[[List of universities in Greece|Greece University System]]<br/>[[Higher education|Higher Education Institution]]\n|endowment = \n|staff =\n|faculty =\n|president =\n|provost =\n|principal = \n|rector =\n|chancellor =\n|vice_chancellor =\n|dean =\n|head_label =\n|head =\n|students =20000 (all campuses)\n|undergrad =\n|postgrad =\n|doctoral =\n|city     = Main campus<br/>[[Lamia (city)|City of Lamia]]<br/>[[Phthiotis|Phthiotis Region]]\n|campus   = Suburban\n|coordinates = {{coord|38|52|30|N|22|26|17|E|type:edu_region:GR|display=inline,title}}\n|colors =\n|colours = \n|mascot =[[Charioteer of Delphi|Heniokhos]] and [[Thermopylae|Thermopyles]] \n|nickname =\n|affiliations = [[University of Thessaly]]<br/>[[University of Limoges]]<br/>[[University of Manchester]]\n|website ={{URL|http://www.teiste.gr}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Technological Educational Institute''' ('''TEI''') '''of Central Greece''' (Greek: \u03a4\u03b5\u03c7\u03bd\u03bf\u03bb\u03bf\u03b3\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc \u0395\u03ba\u03c0\u03b1\u03b9\u03b4\u03b5\u03c5\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc \u038a\u03b4\u03c1\u03c5\u03bc\u03b1 \u03a3\u03c4\u03b5\u03c1\u03b5\u03ac\u03c2 \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1\u03c2) was a university founded in 2013, had a [[Campus university|main campus]] {{convert|15.81|acre|km2}} in the [[Lamia (city)|City of Lamia]], [[Phthiotis]], [[Central Greece (region)|Central Greece]], and four [[Satellite campus|branch campuses]]. The name variants include Technological Institute of Central Greece, Central Greece Institute of Technology, Central Greece University of Applied Sciences, TEI of Central Greece, TEICG, TEISTE. \nA formerly [[higher education|institution of higher education]] of the [[List of universities in Greece|State University System of Greece]], having full self governance and functions under the supervision of the Ministry of Education, Government Gazette Laws 2916/11.6.2001 and 3549/20.3.2007. Technological Institute of Central Greece has abolished on January 29, 2019 and ceased to be a university in its own name status by an Act of Hellenic Parliament, Law 4589/29.01/2019.<ref name=\"Law 4589, 2019, Government Gazette 13 \u0391'/29.01.2019\">{{cite journal|url=https://www.hellenicparliament.gr/Nomothetiko-Ergo/Anazitisi-Nomothetikou-Ergou?law_id=d56f0c5a-1735-48f7-b549-a9c400fa63d7 |title=Law 4589, Government Gazette 13 \u0391'/29.01.2019|publisher=Hellenic Parliament}}{{in lang|el}}, \"Synergies between National and Kapodistrian University of Athens (NKUA), Agricultural University of Athens (AUA), University of Thessaly (UTH) with the TEI of Thessaly and TEI of Central Greece, Panlimniako Fund and other provisions\"</ref><ref name=\"Greece Education System Legislation and Official Policy Documents\">{{cite web|url= https://eacea.ec.europa.eu/national-policies/eurydice/content/legislation-27_en |title=Greece Education System Legislation and Official Policy Documents|publisher=[[Eurydice Network]]}}{{in lang|en}}</ref> Educational departments absorbed by the [[Agricultural University of Athens]] (AUA), [[National and Kapodistrian University of Athens]] (NKUA), [[University of Thessaly]] (UTH).\n \nIt offered 4-year (full-time) [[Undergraduate education|undergraduate]] degree programmes with awarded qualification \u03c0\u03c4\u03c5\u03c7\u03af\u03bf (latinised version: Ptychion), in line with the [[Bologna process]] legally equivalent to a [[Bachelor's degree]], and 1\u00bd years, one-and-a-half-year full-time or 3-year part-time, [[Postgraduate education|postgraduate]] degree programmes with awarded qualification \u03bc\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03c0\u03c4\u03c5\u03c7\u03b9\u03b1\u03ba\u03cc \u03b4\u03af\u03c0\u03bb\u03c9\u03bc\u03b1 \u03b5\u03b9\u03b4\u03af\u03ba\u03b5\u03c5\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2, postgraduate  specialised diploma, legally equivalent to a [[Master's degree]]. The postgraduate programmes have statutory tuition fees.{{efn-ua|name=fn1}} The undergraduate degree studies was formerly 3\u00bd years, three-and-a-half-year, confers a legally equivalent to an Ordinary Bachelor\u2019s Degree (Ord), Pass Bachelor's Degree (Pass).\nAlongside the university, it hosts the Centre of Continuing Education and Lifelong Learning (KEDIVIM; \u039a\u03ad\u03bd\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf \u0395\u03c0\u03b9\u03bc\u03cc\u03c1\u03c6\u03c9\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u0394\u03b9\u03b1 \u0392\u03af\u03bf\u03c5 \u039c\u03ac\u03b8\u03b7\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2; \u039a.\u0395.\u0394\u0399.\u0392\u0399.\u039c.)<ref name=\"University of Thessaly, KEDIVIM, City of Lamia\">{{cite web|url= https://www.diaviou-teiste.gr/ |title=University of Thessaly, KEDIVIM, City of Lamia}} {{in lang|el}} Centre of Continuing Education and Lifelong Learning (KEDIVIM) with the KEK Easy Education</ref><ref name=\"KEK Easy Education\">{{cite web|url= https://www.easy-education.gr/|title=KEK Easy Education}} {{in lang|el}} Centre for Lifelong Learning (KEK)</ref> offers Lifelong Learning courses with tuition fee at on-campus and by [[Distance education|distance e-learning]] off-campus, certified by the National Organization for the Certification of Qualifications and Vocational Guidance (EOPPEP; Greek: \u0395\u03b8\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc\u03c2 \u039f\u03c1\u03b3\u03b1\u03bd\u03b9\u03c3\u03bc\u03cc\u03c2 \u03a0\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c0\u03bf\u03af\u03b7\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2 \u03a0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c3\u03cc\u03bd\u03c4\u03c9\u03bd \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u0395\u03c0\u03b1\u03b3\u03b3\u03b5\u03bb\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03bf\u03cd \u03a0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c3\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03c4\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03c3\u03bc\u03bf\u03cd; \u0395.\u039f.\u03a0.\u03a0.\u0395.\u03a0.) \n__TOC__\n\n==History==\nThe TEI of Larissa was an institution of higher education which was founded in 1983 under Parliament Act 1404/1983 for TEIs. In 1994, the City of Lamia regional campus of the TEI of Larissa became the independent university of the TEI of Lamia awarding its own name degrees. \nIn 2015, TEI of Lamia and the TEI of Chalkida agreed to a merger, Presidential Decree 100, Government Gazette 135 \u0391'/05.06.2013. The founded institution was named TEI of Central Greece with the City of Lamia Campus becoming the university main campus. As the European Union determined, in October 2017 the Ministry of Education specified all TEIs will be merged with the corresponding universities and each TEI department will be absorbed by a corresponding department. On January 17, 2019 the Hellenic Parliamentary Committee Session has voted the submitting draft law on December 28, 2018, and corresponding law 4589 has been published on the Government Gazette No 13 \u0391'/29.01.2019.<ref name=\"Law 4589, 2019, Government Gazette 13 \u0391'/29.01.2019\"/> \n\nThe TEI of Central Greece abolished and admitted its last students in the 2018-2019 [[academic year]]. Subsequently, the [[University of Thessaly]] absorbing the Departments of Computer Science, Electronic Engineering, Nursing, Physiotherapy, and the TEI of Central Greece Main Campus in the City of Lamia was transferred and joined to University of Thessaly at the City of Lamia Campus{{efn-ua|name=fn2}} (that was formerly the main campus of the [[University of Central Greece|University of Central Greece (UTH)]] existed from 2003 to 2013) and became its campus part. Then, due to the integration, the campus is existed into two parts, the North Site and South Site (main).<ref name=\"Greece Open Data Government\">{{cite journal|url=http://www.data.gov.gr/ |title=Greece Open Data Government |publisher=Greece Data Government}} ''Central directory of public data that provides access to databases of Greek government authorities in according to the European Union guide of 2013/37/\u0395U''. {{in lang|el}}</ref><ref name=\"Greece Geodata Government\">{{cite journal|url=http://geodata.gov.gr/ |title=Greece Geodata Government|publisher=}} ''Open geospatial data and services for Greece, serving as a national open data catalogue. Developed in the context of the EU-funded project PublicaMundi, as well as the international Open Source community''. {{in lang|en|el}}</ref><ref name=\"Greece Geodata Government Maps\">{{cite journal|url=http://geodata.gov.gr/maps/?locale=en/ |title=Greece Geodata Government Maps |publisher=Information Management Systems Institute (IMSI) / Research and Innovation Center \"Athena\"}} {{in lang|en|el}}</ref><ref name=\"Greece Open Government\">{{cite journal|url=http://www.opengov.gr/home/ |title=Greece Open Government |publisher=}} [http://www.ydmed.gov.gr/  Minister of Interior] {{in lang|en|el}}</ref><ref name=\"Open Government Partnership Member of Greece\">{{cite journal|url=https://www.opengovpartnership.org/members/greece/ |title=Open Government Partnership Member of Greece |publisher=}}{{in lang|en}}</ref> \"University of Thessaly at the City of Lamia\", \"University of Thessaly, City of Lamia\", is the Branch Campus of the most southerly of the Branch Campuses of the University of Thessaly, {{convert|75.81|mile|km}} south.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"background:transparent;\" \n|-\n| style=\"width:30%; background:#eaecf0;\" align=\"center\" |'''University of Thessaly''' ('''UTH''')\n! style=\"width:40%;\"|Departments{{efn-ua|name=fn3}}\n! style=\"width: