ress: 3rd Km Old National Road Lamia - Athens, 351 32, City of Lamia. At nearby old airport. 4 klm from the city centre. Nea Ampliani District. In the city's South End neighborhood.''<br> ''Map Coordinates'': {{Coord|38|52|30|N|22|26|17|E}}\n|-\n|\n* Department of Physiotherapy<ref name=\"University of Thessaly, Department of Physiotherapy\">{{cite web|url=http://phys.teiste.gr/ |title=University of Thessaly, Department of Physiotherapy}}{{in lang|el}}</ref>  \n|- \n| align=\"center\"  style=\"background:#eaecf0;\"|'''General Department''' ('''postgraduate''') \n|-\n|\n*Advanced Physiotherapy<ref name=\"University of Thessaly, Advanced Physiotherapy Postgraduate Program\">{{cite web|url=http://mscphysio.teiste.gr/ |title=University of Thessaly, Advanced Physiotherapy Postgraduate Program}} {{in lang|el}} \"General Department (postgraduate programs)\"</ref>{{efn-ua|name=fn1}}\n|- class=\"expand-child\"\n|colspan=\"3\" | {{small| The General Department refers to a Division of Graduate Studies or [[Graduate School]] offers postgraduate programs with granted qualification \u03bc\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03c0\u03c4\u03c5\u03c7\u03b9\u03b1\u03ba\u03cc \u03b4\u03af\u03c0\u03bb\u03c9\u03bc\u03b1 \u03b5\u03b9\u03b4\u03af\u03ba\u03b5\u03c5\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2 (\u039c\u0394\u0395), postgraduate specialised diploma, equivalent to a Master's degree.}} {{small|Not to be confused with [[Postgraduate diploma|Postgraduate Diploma]] (PGDip). A postgraduate diploma typically has 120 ECTS of postgraduate courses, whereas a full master's degree is usually 180 ECTS.}} {{small|The Departments of Computer Science and Telecommunications, and Computer Science and Biomedical Informatics offer in collaboration the Interdepartmental postgraduate degree program in Informatics and Computational Biomedicine.}} {{small|The campus refers to the two sites of the north and the south into which the campus is divided.}}\n|}\n\n==Organisation==\nThe academic year is divided in two semesters, a semester lasts 13 full weeks and it can be extended up to two weeks, Law 4009/2011, Government Gazette 195/A, 06.09.2011. One academic year corresponds to 60 [[European Credit Transfer and Accumulation System|ECTS]] credit points (Greek: \u03a0\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03c9\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ad\u03c2 \u039c\u03bf\u03bd\u03ac\u03b4\u03b5\u03c2 \u03a0\u039c, \u039c\u03bf\u03bd\u03ac\u03b4\u03b5\u03c2 \u03a6\u03cc\u03c1\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u0395\u03c1\u03b3\u03b1\u03c3\u03af\u03b1\u03c2). For [[UNESCO]]'s ISCED<ref name=\"International Standard Classification of Education (ISCED) 2011\">{{cite web|url=http://uis.unesco.org/sites/default/files/documents/international-standard-classification-of-education-isced-2011-en.pdf |title=International Standard Classification of Education (ISCED) 2011 |publisher=Unesco Organization}}{{in lang|en}}</ref><ref name=\"ISCED-F 2013 Fields of education and training \u2013 Detailed field descriptions\">{{cite web|url=http://uis.unesco.org/sites/default/files/documents/international-standard-classification-of-education-fields-of-education-and-training-2013-detailed-field-descriptions-2015-en.pdf |title=ISCED-F 2013 Fields of education and training \u2013 Detailed field descriptions |publisher=Unesco Organization}}{{in lang|en}}</ref> [[International Standard Classification of Education]], [[European Qualifications Framework]] (EQF), and [[National qualifications framework|National Qualification Framework]] (NQF) of Greece named Hellenic Qualification Framework (HQF),<ref name=\"Hellenic Qualifications Framework (HQF)\">{{cite web|url=http://proson.eoppep.gr/en/QualificationTypes|title=Hellenic Qualifications Framework (HQF)|publisher=EOPPEP Organisation}} ''National Qualification Framework (NQF) of Greece'' {{in lang|el|en}}</ref><ref name=\"Hellenic Qualification Framework (HQF)\">{{cite journal|url=https://www.nqf.gov.gr/ |title=Hellenic Qualification Framework (HQF)|publisher=Hellenic Qualification Framework}}{{in lang|el}}</ref> the classification of qualification level for Bachelor\u201bs degree (240 ECTS, pass degree 210 ECTS) is at Level 6 and for Master\u201bs degree (90 ECTS) is at Level 7. The Senior Project has 20 ECTS. A graduate of specially engineering disciplines only, it can hold the state-granted and approved professional title of \"Licensed Engineer\", when meet the criteria and pass the qualification exams by the National Engineering Accreditation Council of Greece State Department of Regulatory Authority. A professional qualification is indicated by the [[Post-nominal letters|post-nominals]] LEng designation authorizes a [[Regulation and licensure in engineering|regulation]] and [[licensure]] in engineering with a number of register ID license. Technological Educational Institute engineering graduate is a graduate engineer, technology or technological engineer, known as engineering [[Engineering technologist|technologist]]. The Licensed Engineer LEng (registered engineer, a prerequisite licence to practicing) should not be confused with Graduate Engineer (academically qualified) which is legally regulated and limited to [[List of universities in Greece|Higher Education Institution (HEI)]] graduate.  \n<!-- Please respect, only official data to articles for the actual Central Greece Institute of Technology (CGIT) not just the subject in general, also do not insert URL links directly to the department or faculty listing-->\n\n====Specialisation semester====\nThe Co-operative Education Employment-integrated Programme ([[Curriculum|curricular]] [[internship]]), also known as specialisation semester of supervised work [[practicum]], is an off-campus undergraduate semester where the student is a trainee-in-practice has employment and practical training for 10 ECTS credits, 960 hours (8 hours a day, 5 days a week, 24 consecutive weeks) in a specialised subject of free-choice. It can also be a concentration splits into specialisations within the internship subject. TEI Internship is a government subsidy industry placement of fixed-term contract for students recruited by employers. The students should find itself an internship term placement. TEIs are not responsible for finding internships. The Educational Collaboration Agreement of internship is a paid [[Fixed-term employment contract|CDD]] [[employment contract]] signed between a student (intern; student qualifies as trainee), and the co-op (cooperative) employer, accredited by the university, under the tutelage of a supervised TEI professor. It is funded by the Workforce Employment Organisation of Greece - OAED (Greek: [[:el: \u039f\u03c1\u03b3\u03b1\u03bd\u03b9\u03c3\u03bc\u03cc\u03c2 \u0391\u03c0\u03b1\u03c3\u03c7\u03bf\u03bb\u03ae\u03c3\u03b5\u03c9\u03c2 \u0395\u03c1\u03b3\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03bf\u03cd \u0394\u03c5\u03bd\u03b1\u03bc\u03b9\u03ba\u03bf\u03cd|\u039f\u0391\u0395\u0394]]). The co-op employer must register internship student into the Social Security System, while at the internship end receives reimbursement.\n\n====\u0395xchange programme====\nAn exchange student is an incoming from abroad or outgoing to abroad, at an affiliated HE Institution of the TEI of Central Greece.\nThe duration of exchange is 1 term (semester) or 1 academic year, while Greek is the official language of instruction. The affiliated institution can be a partner HEI located in [[Erasmus Programme|Erasmus]] partner countries through inter-institutional agreements between HEIs.<ref name=\"EU Erasmus Plus Higher Education Charter\">{{cite web|url=https://ec.europa.eu/programmes/erasmus-plus/resources/documents/applicants/higher-education-charter_en |title=EU Erasmus Plus Higher Education Charter|publisher=European Commission}}{{in lang|en}}</ref><ref name=\"EU Erasmus Plus Programme University of Thessaly (UTH)\">{{cite web|url=http://erasmus.uth.gr/en/ |title=EU Erasmus Plus Programme University of Thessaly (UTH)|publisher=University of Thessaly (UTH)}}{{in lang|en|el}}</ref> It generally requires a [[Common European Framework of Reference for Languages#Language-specific scales|B2 English]] Language Level (the level is according to the Common European Framework of Reference for Languages -CEFR), unless it is stated otherwise in the Inter-Institutional Agreement. The B2 English Language level is equivalent to a total score of 72 in TOEFL or a total score 6 score in IELTS. Before applying to the TEICG's Erasmus Office, it needs to be nominated by student's home university having a valid bilateral agreement between student\u2019s Home Institution and TEICG Institution. Erasmus [[European Union|EU]]/[[European Free Trade Association|EFTA]] and Non-EU student prior should obtain the [[European Health Insurance Card]] (EHIC) in its home country. If it does not have national health insurance in its home country (it cannot obtain the European Health Insurance Card) then it has two options, it can purchase health insurance in its home country or join the Greece National Health System. Students have to make accommodation and visa arrangements by themselves. The TEICG holds a student restaurant in its South Site where Erasmus students can have breakfast, midday and evening meal at a reduced price. The [[Erasmus Student Network]] (ESN) Greece is a non-profit organization.<ref name=\"Erasmus Student Network (ESN) Greece\">{{cite web|url=https://esngreece.gr|title=Erasmus Student Network (ESN) Greece}}{{in lang|en}}</ref><ref name=\"Help and advice for EU nationals and their family\">{{cite journal|url=https://europa.eu/youreurope/citizens/index_en.htm |title=Help and advice for EU nationals and their family |publisher=European Commission}} ''Travel, Work retirement, Vehicles, Resident formalities, Education, Health, Consumer'' {{in lang|en|el}}</ref><ref name=\"JoinUp by European Commission\">{{cite journal|url= https://joinup.ec.europa.eu/solutions/ |title=JoinUp by European Commission |publisher=}}{{in lang|en}}</ref>\n\n===Academics===\n\n===Undergraduate===  \n{{col-begin|width=90%}} \n{{col-2}}\n