tisi-Nomothetikou-Ergou?law_id=26e249e2-9bda-4411-977f-a7b7015f6ba7 |title=Law 4485/2017 Government Gazette 114 \u0391'/04.08.2017|publisher=Hellenic Parliament}}</ref>}}\n{{efn-ua|name=fn2| \nThe Department of Computer Science and Telecommunications is since 2019, it formerly was named the Department of Computer Science 2013 to 2018.<br/>The Department of Computer Science and Biomedical Informatics is since 2004-2005 academic year.}}\n{{efn-ua|name=fn3|[[University of Thessaly#Faculties and departments|University of Thessaly (UTH) Faculties and Departments]]}}\n}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.teiste.gr Official website]\n\n{{Universities in Greece}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List Of Universities In Greece}}\n[[Category:Technological educational institutions in Greece]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox university\n|name =Technological Educational Institute <br/>of Central Greece\n|native_name =\u03a4\u03b5\u03c7\u03bd\u03bf\u03bb\u03bf\u03b3\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc \u0395\u03ba\u03c0\u03b1\u03b9\u03b4\u03b5\u03c5\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc \u038a\u03b4\u03c1\u03c5\u03bc\u03b1 <br/>\u03a3\u03c4\u03b5\u03c1\u03b5\u03ac\u03c2 \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1\u03c2\n|former_names =Technological Educational Institute of Lamia <br/>(1994\u20132013)<br/>\nTechnological Educational Institute of Larissa at the <br/>City of Lamia <br/>(1983\u20131994)\n|established =2019 \u2013 Abolished<br>2013 \u2013 Technological Educational Institute <br/>of Central Greece\n\n|type=[[Public university|Public University]]<br/>[[List of universities in Greece|Greece University System]]<br/>[[Higher education|Higher Education Institution]]\n|endowment = \n|staff =\n|faculty =\n|president =\n|provost =\n|principal = \n|rector =\n|chancellor =\n|vice_chancellor =\n|dean =\n|head_label =\n|head =\n|students =20000 (all campuses)\n|undergrad =\n|postgrad =\n|doctoral =\n|city     = Main campus<br/>[[Lamia (city)|City of Lamia]]<br/>[[Phthiotis|Phthiotis Region]]\n|campus   = Suburban\n|coordinates = {{coord|38|52|30|N|22|26|17|E|type:edu_region:GR|display=inline,title}}\n|colors =\n|colours = \n|mascot =[[Charioteer of Delphi|Heniokhos]] and [[Thermopylae|Thermopyles]] \n|nickname =\n|affiliations = [[University of Thessaly]]<br/>[[University of Limoges]]<br/>[[University of Manchester]]\n|website ={{URL|http://www.teiste.gr}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Technological Educational Institute''' ('''TEI''') '''of Central Greece''' (Greek: \u03a4\u03b5\u03c7\u03bd\u03bf\u03bb\u03bf\u03b3\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc \u0395\u03ba\u03c0\u03b1\u03b9\u03b4\u03b5\u03c5\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc \u038a\u03b4\u03c1\u03c5\u03bc\u03b1 \u03a3\u03c4\u03b5\u03c1\u03b5\u03ac\u03c2 \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1\u03c2) was a university founded in 2013, had a [[Campus university|main campus]] {{convert|15.81|acre|km2}} in the [[Lamia (city)|City of Lamia]], [[Phthiotis]], [[Central Greece (region)|Central Greece]], and four [[Satellite campus|branch campuses]]. The name variants include Technological Institute of Central Greece, Central Greece Institute of Technology, Central Greece University of Applied Sciences, TEI of Central Greece, TEICG, TEISTE. \nA formerly [[higher education|institution of higher education]] of the [[List of universities in Greece|State University System of Greece]], having full self governance and functions under the supervision of the Ministry of Education, Government Gazette Laws 2916/11.6.2001 and 3549/20.3.2007. Technological Institute of Central Greece has abolished on January 29, 2019 and ceased to be a university in its own name status by an Act of Hellenic Parliament, Law 4589/29.01/2019.<ref name=\"Law 4589, 2019, Government Gazette 13 \u0391'/29.01.2019\">{{cite journal|url=https://www.hellenicparliament.gr/Nomothetiko-Ergo/Anazitisi-Nomothetikou-Ergou?law_id=d56f0c5a-1735-48f7-b549-a9c400fa63d7 |title=Law 4589, Government Gazette 13 \u0391'/29.01.2019|publisher=Hellenic Parliament}}{{in lang|el}}, \"Synergies between National and Kapodistrian University of Athens (NKUA), Agricultural University of Athens (AUA), University of Thessaly (UTH) with the TEI of Thessaly and TEI of Central Greece, Panlimniako Fund and other provisions\"</ref><ref name=\"Greece Education System Legislation and Official Policy Documents\">{{cite web|url= https://eacea.ec.europa.eu/national-policies/eurydice/content/legislation-27_en |title=Greece Education System Legislation and Official Policy Documents|publisher=[[Eurydice Network]]}}{{in lang|en}}</ref> Educational departments absorbed by the [[Agricultural University of Athens]] (AUA), [[National and Kapodistrian University of Athens]] (NKUA), [[University of Thessaly]] (UTH).\n \nIt offered 4-year (full-time) [[Undergraduate education|undergraduate]] degree programmes with awarded qualification \u03c0\u03c4\u03c5\u03c7\u03af\u03bf (latinised version: Ptychion), in line with the [[Bologna process]] legally equivalent to a [[Bachelor's degree]], and 1\u00bd years, one-and-a-half-year full-time or 3-year part-time, [[Postgraduate education|postgraduate]] degree programmes with awarded qualification \u03bc\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03c0\u03c4\u03c5\u03c7\u03b9\u03b1\u03ba\u03cc \u03b4\u03af\u03c0\u03bb\u03c9\u03bc\u03b1 \u03b5\u03b9\u03b4\u03af\u03ba\u03b5\u03c5\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2, postgraduate  specialised diploma, legally equivalent to a [[Master's degree]]. The postgraduate programmes have statutory tuition fees.{{efn-ua|name=fn1}} The undergraduate degree studies was formerly 3\u00bd years, three-and-a-half-year, confers a legally equivalent to an Ordinary Bachelor\u2019s Degree (Ord), Pass Bachelor's Degree (Pass).\nAlongside the university, it hosts the Centre of Continuing Education and Lifelong Learning (KEDIVIM; \u039a\u03ad\u03bd\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf \u0395\u03c0\u03b9\u03bc\u03cc\u03c1\u03c6\u03c9\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u0394\u03b9\u03b1 \u0392\u03af\u03bf\u03c5 \u039c\u03ac\u03b8\u03b7\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2; \u039a.\u0395.\u0394\u0399.\u0392\u0399.\u039c.)<ref name=\"University of Thessaly, KEDIVIM, City of Lamia\">{{cite web|url= https://www.diaviou-teiste.gr/ |title=University of Thessaly, KEDIVIM, City of Lamia}} {{in lang|el}} Centre of Continuing Education and Lifelong Learning (KEDIVIM) with the KEK Easy Education</ref><ref name=\"KEK Easy Education\">{{cite web|url= https://www.easy-education.gr/|title=KEK Easy Education}} {{in lang|el}} Centre for Lifelong Learning (KEK)</ref> offers Lifelong Learning courses with tuition fee at on-campus and by [[Distance education|distance e-learning]] off-campus, certified by the National Organization for the Certification of Qualifications and Vocational Guidance (EOPPEP; Greek: \u0395\u03b8\u03bd\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc\u03c2 \u039f\u03c1\u03b3\u03b1\u03bd\u03b9\u03c3\u03bc\u03cc\u03c2 \u03a0\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03bf\u03c0\u03bf\u03af\u03b7\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2 \u03a0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c3\u03cc\u03bd\u03c4\u03c9\u03bd \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u0395\u03c0\u03b1\u03b3\u03b3\u03b5\u03bb\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03bf\u03cd \u03a0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c3\u03b1\u03bd\u03b1\u03c4\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03c3\u03bc\u03bf\u03cd; \u0395.\u039f.\u03a0.\u03a0.\u0395.\u03a0.) \n__TOC__\n\n==History==\nThe TEI of Larissa was an institution of higher education which was founded in 1983 under Parliament Act 1404/1983 for TEIs. In 1994, the City of Lamia regional campus of the TEI of Larissa became the independent university of the TEI of Lamia awarding its own name degrees. \nIn 2015, TEI of Lamia and the TEI of Chalkida agreed to a merger, Presidential Decree 100, Government Gazette 135 \u0391'/05.06.2013. The founded institution was named TEI of Central Greece with the City of Lamia Campus becoming the university main campus. As the European Union determined, in October 2017 the Ministry of Education specified all TEIs will be merged with the corresponding universities and each TEI department will be absorbed by a corresponding department. On January 17, 2019 the Hellenic Parliamentary Committee Session has voted the submitting draft law on December 28, 2018, and corresponding law 4589 has been published on the Government Gazette No 13 \u0391'/29.01.2019.<ref name=\"Law 4589, 2019, Government Gazette 13 \u0391'/29.01.2019\"/> \n\nThe TEI of Central Greece abolished and admitted its last students in the 2018-2019 [[academic year]]. Subsequently, the [[University of Thessaly]] absorbing the Departments of Computer Science, Electronic Engineering, Nursing, Physiotherapy, and the TEI of Central Greece Main Campus in the City of Lamia was transferred and joined to University of Thessaly at the City of Lamia Campus{{efn-ua|name=fn2}} (that was formerly the main campus of the [[University of Central Greece|University of Central Greece (UTH)]] existed from 2003 to 2013) and became its campus part. Then, due to the integration, the campus is existed into two parts, the North Site and South Site (main).<ref name=\"Greece Open Data Government\">{{cite journal|url=http://www.data.gov.gr/ |title=Greece Open Data Government |publisher=Greece Data Government}} ''Central directory of public data that provides access to databases of Greek government authorities in according to the European Union guide of 2013/37/\u0395U''. {{in lang|el}}</ref><ref name=\"Greece Geodata Government\">{{cite journal|url=http://geodata.gov.gr/ |title=Greece Geodata Government|publisher=}} ''Open geospatial data and services for Greece, serving as a national open data catalogue. Developed in the context of the EU-funded project PublicaMundi, as well as the international Open Source community''. {{in lang|en|el}}</ref><ref name=\"Greece Geodata Government Maps\">{{cite journal|url=http://geodata.gov.gr/maps/?locale=en/ |title=Greece Geodata Government Maps |publisher=Information Management Systems Institute (IMSI) / Research and Innovation Center \"Athena\"}} {{in lang|en|el}}</ref><ref name=\"Greece Open Government\">{{cite journal|url=http://www.opengov.gr/home/ |title=Greece Open Government |publisher=}} [http://www.ydmed.gov.gr/  Minister of Interior] {{in lang|en|el}}</ref><ref name=\"Open Government Partnership Member of Greece\">{{cite journal|url=https://www.opengovpartnership.org/members/greece/ |title=Open Government Partnership Member of Greece |publisher=}}{{in lang|en}}</ref> \"University of Thessaly at the City of Lamia\", \"University of Thessaly, City of Lamia\", is the Branch Campus of the most southerly of the Branch Campuses of the University of Thessaly, {{convert|75.81|mile|km}} south.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"background:transparent;\" \n|-\n| style=\"width:30%; background:#eaecf0;\" align=\"center\" |'''University of Thessaly''' ('''UTH''')\n! style=\"width:40%;\"|Departments{{efn-ua|name=fn3}}\n! style=\"width:30%;\"|Campus  \n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | '''Faculty of Science'''<ref name=\"University of Thessaly, School of Sciences\">{{cite web|url=http://sci.uth.gr/ |title=University of Thessaly, School of Science}}{{in lang|el}}</ref>\n| \n* Department of Physics\n* Department of Mathematics \n* Department of Computer Science and Telecommunications\n* Department of Computer Science and Biomedical Informatics\n| rowspan=\"3\" | ''North Site<ref name=\"University of Thessaly, City of Lamia, North Site Campus\">{{cite web|url=http://sci.uth.gr/|title=University of Thessaly, City of Lamia, North Site Campus }}{{in lang|el}}</ref> (urban). Address: 2-4 Papasiopoulou str, 351 31, City of Lamia. Attached to the 16th Primary School\u2019s building. At nearby St. Michael and Gabriel's Hill park. 300 m close to Town Hall (city's council). 1.2 klm from the city centre. Galaneika District. 5 klm from South Site.'' \n''Map Coordinates'': {{Coord|38|54|45|N|22|25|41|E}}\n|- \n| align=\"center\" style=\"background:#eaecf0;\"|'''General Department''' ('''postgraduate''') \n|-\n|\n* Informatics and Computational Biomedicine<ref name=\"University of Thessaly, Informatics and Computational Biomedicine Postgraduate Program\">{{cite web|url=http://icb.sci.uth.gr/ |title=University of Thessaly, Informatics and Computational Biomedicine Postgraduate Program}} {{in lang|el}} \"General Department (postgraduate programs)\"</ref>{{efn-ua|name=fn1}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | '''Faculty of Health Sciences'''<ref name=\"University of Thessaly, School of Health Sciences\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sey.uth.gr/|title=University of Thessaly, School of Health Sciences}}{{in lang|el}}</ref>  \n| align=\"center\" style=\"background:#eaecf0;\"|'''Departments'''{{efn-ua|name=fn3}}\n| rowspan=\"4\" | ''South Site<ref name=\"University of Thessaly, City of Lamia, South Site Campus\">{{cite web|url=http://www.teiste.gr/ |title=University of Thessaly, City of Lamia, South Site Campus}}{{in lang|el}}</ref> (suburban). Address: 3rd Km Old National Road Lamia - Athens, 351 32, City of Lamia. At nearby old airport. 4 klm from the city centre. Nea Ampliani District. In the city's South End neighborhood.''<br> ''Map Coordinates'': {{Coord|38|52|30|N|22|26|17|E}}\n|-\n|\n* Department of Physiotherapy<ref name=\"University of Thessaly, Department of Physiotherapy\">{{cite web|url=http://phys.teiste.gr/ |title=University of Thessaly, Department of Physiotherapy}}{{in lang|el}}</ref>  \n|- \n| align=\"center\"  style=\"background:#eaecf0;\"|'''General Department''' ('''postgraduate''') \n|-\n|\n*Advanced Physiotherapy<ref name=\"University of Thessaly, Advanced Physiotherapy Postgraduate Program\">{{cite web|url=http://mscphysio.teiste.gr/ |title=University of Thessaly, Advanced Physiotherapy Postgraduate Program}} {{in lang|el}} \"General Department (postgraduate programs)\"</ref>{{efn-ua|name=fn1}}\n|- class=\"expand-child\"\n|colspan=\"3\" | {{small| The General Department refers to a Division of Graduate Studies or [[Graduate School]] offers postgraduate programs with granted qualification \u03bc\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03c0\u03c4\u03c5\u03c7\u03b9\u03b1\u03ba\u03cc \u03b4\u03af\u03c0\u03bb\u03c9\u03bc\u03b1 \u03b5\u03b9\u03b4\u03af\u03ba\u03b5\u03c5\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2 (\u039c\u0394\u0395), postgraduate specialised diploma, equivalent to a Master's degree.}} {{small|Not to be confused with [[Postgraduate diploma|Postgraduate Diploma]] (PGDip). A postgraduate diploma typically has 120 ECTS of postgraduate courses, whereas a full master's degree is usually 180 ECTS.}} {{small|The Departments of Computer Science and Telecommunications, and Computer Science and Biomedical Informatics offer in collaboration the Interdepartmental postgraduate degree program in Informatics and Computational Biomedicine.}} {{small|The campus refers to the two sites of the north and the south into which the campus is divided.}}\n|}\n\n==Organisation==\nThe academic year is divided in two semesters, a semester lasts 13 full weeks and it can be extended up to two weeks, Law 4009/2011, Government Gazette 195/A, 06.09.2011. One academic year corresponds to 60 [[European Credit Transfer and Accumulation System|ECTS]] credit points (Greek: \u03a0\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03c9\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ad\u03c2 \u039c\u03bf\u03bd\u03ac\u03b4\u03b5\u03c2 \u03a0\u039c, \u039c\u03bf\u03bd\u03ac\u03b4\u03b5\u03c2 \u03a6\u03cc\u03c1\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u0395\u03c1\u03b3\u03b1\u03c3\u03af\u03b1\u03c2). For [[UNESCO]]'s ISCED<ref name=\"International Standard Classification of Education (ISCED) 2011\">{{cite web|url=http://uis.unesco.org/sites/default/files/documents/international-standard-classification-of-education-isced-2011-en.pdf |title=International Standard Classification of Education (ISCED) 2011 |publisher=Unesco Organization}}{{in lang|en}}</ref><ref name=\"ISCED-F 2013 Fields of education and training \u2013 Detailed field descriptions\">{{cite web|url=http://uis.unesco.org/sites/default/files/documents/international-standard-classification-of-education-fields-of-education-and-training-2013-detailed-field-descriptions-2015-en.pdf |title=ISCED-F 2013 Fields of education and training \u2013 Detailed field descriptions |publisher=Unesco Organization}}{{in lang|en}}</ref> [[International Standard Classification of Education]], [[European Qualifications Framework]] (EQF), and [[National qualifications framework|National Qualification Framework]] (NQF) of Greece named Hellenic Qualification Framework (HQF),<ref name=\"Hellenic Qualifications Framework (HQF)\">{{cite web|url=http://proson.eoppep.gr/en/QualificationTypes|title=Hellenic Qualifications Framework (HQF)|publisher=EOPPEP Organisation}} ''National Qualification Framework (NQF) of Greece'' {{in lang|el|en}}</ref><ref name=\"Hellenic Qualification Framework (HQF)\">{{cite journal|url=https://www.nqf.gov.gr/ |title=Hellenic Qualification Framework (HQF)|publisher=Hellenic Qualification Framework}}{{in lang|el}}</ref> the classification of qualification level for Bachelor\u201bs degree (240 ECTS, pass degree 210 ECTS) is at Level 6 and for Master\u201bs degree (90 ECTS) is at Level 7. The Senior Project has 20 ECTS. A graduate of specially engineering disciplines only, it can hold the state-granted and approved professional title of \"Licensed Engineer\", when meet the criteria and pass the qualification exams by the National Engineering Accreditation Council of Greece State Department of Regulatory Authority. A professional qualification is indicated by the [[Post-nominal letters|post-nominals]] LEng designation authorizes a [[Regulation and licensure in engineering|regulation]] and [[licensure]] in engineering with a number of register ID license. Technological Educational Institute engineering graduate is a graduate engineer, technology or technological engineer, known as engineering [[Engineering technologist|technologist]]. The Licensed Engineer LEng (registered engineer, a prerequisite licence to practicing) should not be confused with Graduate Engineer (academically qualified) which is legally regulated and limited to [[List of universities in Greece|Higher Education Institution (HEI)]] graduate.  \n<!-- Please respect, only official data to articles for the actual Central Greece Institute of Technology (CGIT) not just the subject in general, also do not insert URL links directly to the department or faculty listing-->\n\n====Specialisation semester====\nThe Co-operative Education Employment-integrated Programme ([[Curriculum|curricular]] [[internship]]), also known as specialisation semester of supervised work [[practicum]], is an off-campus undergraduate semester where the student is a trainee-in-practice has employment and practical training for 10 ECTS credits, 960 hours (8 hours a day, 5 days a week, 24 consecutive weeks) in a specialised subject of free-choice. It can also be a concentration splits into specialisations within the internship subject. TEI Internship is a government subsidy industry placement of fixed-term contract for students recruied by employers. The students should find itself an internship term placement. TEIs are not responsible for finding internships. The Educational Collaboration Agreement of internship is a paid [[Fixed-term employment contract|CDD]] [[employment contract]] signed between a student (intern; student qualifies as trainee), and the co-op (cooperative) employer, accredited by the university, under the tutelage of a supervised TEI professor. It is funded by the Workforce Employment Organisation of Greece - OAED (Greek: [[:el: \u039f\u03c1\u03b3\u03b1\u03bd\u03b9\u03c3\u03bc\u03cc\u03c2 \u0391\u03c0\u03b1\u03c3\u03c7\u03bf\u03bb\u03ae\u03c3\u03b5\u03c9\u03c2 \u0395\u03c1\u03b3\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03bf\u03cd \u0394\u03c5\u03bd\u03b1\u03bc\u03b9\u03ba\u03bf\u03cd|\u039f\u0391\u0395\u0394]]). The co-op employer must register internship student into the Social Security System, while at the internship end receives reimbursement.\n\n====\u0395xchange programme====\nAn exchange student is an incoming from abroad or outgoing to abroad, at an affiliated HE Institution of the TEI of Central Greece.\nThe duration of exchange is 1 term (semester) or 1 academic year, while Greek is the official language of instruction. The affiliated institution can be a partner HEI located in [[Erasmus Programme|Erasmus]] partner countries through inter-institutional agreements between HEIs.<ref name=\"EU Erasmus Plus Higher Education Charter\">{{cite web|url=https://ec.europa.eu/programmes/erasmus-plus/resources/documents/applicants/higher-education-charter_en |title=EU Erasmus Plus Higher Education Charter|publisher=European Commission}}{{in lang|en}}</ref><ref name=\"EU Erasmus Plus Programme University of Thessaly (UTH)\">{{cite web|url=http://erasmus.uth.gr/en/ |title=EU Erasmus Plus Programme University of Thessaly (UTH)|publisher=University of Thessaly (UTH)}}{{in lang|en|el}}</ref> It generally requires a [[Common European Framework of Reference for Languages#Language-specific scales|B2 English]] Language Level (the level is according to the Common European Framework of Reference for Languages -CEFR), unless it is stated otherwise in the Inter-Institutional Agreement. The B2 English Language level is equivalent to a total score of 72 in TOEFL or a total score 6 score in IELTS. Before applying to the TEICG's Erasmus Office, it needs to be nominated by student's home university having a valid bilateral agreement between student\u2019s Home Institution and TEICG Institution. Erasmus [[European Union|EU]]/[[European Free Trade Association|EFTA]] and Non-EU student prior should obtain the [[European Health Insurance Card]] (EHIC) in its home country. If it does not have national health insurance in its home country (it cannot obtain the European Health Insurance Card) then it has two options, it can purchase health insurance in its home country or join the Greece National Health System. Students have to make accommodation and visa arrangements by themselves. The TEICG holds a student restaurant in its South Site where Erasmus students can have breakfast, midday and evening meal at a reduced price. The [[Erasmus Student Network]] (ESN) Greece is a non-profit organization.<ref name=\"Erasmus Student Network (ESN) Greece\">{{cite web|url=https://esngreece.gr|title=Erasmus Student Network (ESN) Greece}}{{in lang|en}}</ref><ref name=\"Help and advice for EU nationals and their family\">{{cite journal|url=https://europa.eu/youreurope/citizens/index_en.htm |title=Help and advice for EU nationals and their family |publisher=European Commission}} ''Travel, Work retirement, Vehicles, Resident formalities, Education, Health, Consumer'' {{in lang|en|el}}</ref><ref name=\"JoinUp by European Commission\">{{cite journal|url= https://joinup.ec.europa.eu/solutions/ |title=JoinUp by European Commission |publisher=}}{{in lang|en}}</ref>\n\n===Academics===\n\n===Undergraduate===  \n{{col-begin|width=90%}} \n{{col-2}}\n; Faculty of Health and Caring \n* Department of Nursing\n* Department of Physiotherapy\n{{col-2}}\n; Campuses \n* City of Lamia, Phthiotis Region\n* City of Lamia, Phthiotis Region\n{{col-end}} \n{{col-begin|width=90%}} \n{{col-2}}\n; Faculty of Technological Applications \n* Department of Computer Science\n* Department of Aircraft Engineering\n* Department of Electrical Engineering \n* Department of Electronic Engineering \n* Department of Automation Engineering \n* Department of Mechanical Engineering \n{{col-2}}\n; Campuses \n* City of Lamia, Phthiotis Region \n* Psachna, Euboea Region\n* Psachna, Euboea Region \n* City of Lamia, Phthiotis Region\n* Psachna, Euboea Region\n* Psachna, Euboea Region \n{{col-end}}\n{{col-begin|width=90%}} \n{{col-2}}\n; Faculty of Business and Economics \n* Department of Marketing\n* Department of Logistics Management\n* Department of Business Administration \n* Department of Accounting and Finance\n* Department of Culture and Tourism Business Management\n{{col-2}}\n; Campuses \n* Amfissa, Phocis Region\n* Thebes, Boeotia Region\n* Psachna, Euboea Region\n* Psachna, Euboea Region\n* Amfissa, Phocis Region \n{{col-end}}\n{{col-begin|width=90%}} \n{{col-2}}\n; Faculty of Agriculture Technology, Food Techn