nal Europass Centre (NEC) of Greece, the EOPPEP organisation. A Diploma Supplement (DS) is an accredited document has a standardised description of the content and status of the studies completed by its holder that are commonly easily understood, especially outside the country where they were awarded  \u2013 it is not a substitute qualification for the original, nor a CV, nor guarantee recognition.\n\n== See also ==\n* [https://pki.ermis.gov.gr/repository_en.html   ERMIS \u2013 Certificate Authority] ''Certification Authority for Digital Certificates for Citizens'' {{in lang|en}}\n* [http://www.doatap.gr/en/  DOATAP] \u2013 ''Greece NARIC / Academic Recognition and Information Centre'' {{in lang|el|en}} \n* [https://e-doatap.doatap.gr/ e-DOATAP \u2013 Online Application for Foreign Academic Qualification Accreditation] {{in lang|en}}\n* [https://nilde.heal-link.gr  HEAL Link] \u2013 ''Electronic Documents Delivery Service of Scientific Articles'' {{in lang|el|en}}\n* [https://eudoxus.gr/  EUDOXUS] ''Online Integrated Textbook Management Service for University Students''. {{in lang|el}}\n* EUDOXUS ''Textbooks-Distribution, as service desks for the delivery of academic textbooks''\n* EUDOXUS ''Textbooks-Returns, as service desks for returns of wrongly delivered textbooks''\n* EUDOXUS ''Textbooks-Borrowing, as service desks for borrowing academic textbooks''\n* [https://www.eetem.gr/  EETEM] - ''National Society of Higher Education Engineers Technologists Guild''\n* [http://aped.gov.gr/ \u0391PED \u2013 Digital Signature] ''Certification Authority of the Hellenic State'' {{in lang|el}}\n* [http://amelib.seab.gr/?lang=en  AMELib] \u2013 ''Accessible Multi-modal Electronic Library \u2013 Book Search Help Desk''\n* [https://www.heal-link.gr/?lang=en Hellenic Academic Libraries Link (HEAL\u2013Link)] {{in lang|el|en}}\n* [http://www.unioncatalog.gr/index.php?lang=en Union Catalog Hellenic Academic Libraries] {{in lang|el|en}}\n* [https://el.wikibooks.org/wiki/\u0394\u03b5\