ch can be attended without any payment of tuition fee. <br />Especially, about 1 out of the 4 (one-fourth of) HEIs postgraduate programmes offered free without tuition fee, and also a 30% percentage of students can be entitled without <br />tuition fee (non fee-paying students) to attend all the statutory tuition fee postgraduate programmes after they be assessed on an individual basis of criteria as set out in the <br/>Ministerial Decree 13175/Z1/10.08.2018 of Ministry of Education in the Government Gazette 3387 B\u2019/10.8.2018, and law 4485/2017 Government Gazette 114 \u0391'/04.08.2017.<ref name=\"Law 4485/2017 Government Gazette 114 \u0391'/04.08.2017\">{{cite journal|url=https://www.hellenicparliament.gr/Nomothetiko-Ergo/Anazitisi-Nomothetikou-Ergou?law_id=26e249e2-9bda-4411-977f-a7b7015f6ba7 |title=Law 4485/2017 Government Gazette 114 \u0391'/04.08.2017|publisher=Hellenic Parliament}}</ref>}}\n{{efn-ua|name=fn2| \nThe Department of Computer Science and Telecommunications is since 2019, it formerly was named the Department of Computer Science 2013 to 2018.<br/>The Department of Computer Science and Biomedical Informatics is since 2004-2005 academic year.}}\n{{efn-ua|name=fn3|[[University of Thessaly#Faculties and departments|University of Thessaly (UTH) Faculties and Departments]]}}\n}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.teiste.gr Official website]\n\n{{Universities in Greece}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:List Of Universities In Greece}}\n[[Category:Technological educational institutions in Greece]]\n", "name_user": "Bellowhead678", "label": "safe", "comment": "recruied->recruited -Fix a typo in one click", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Technological_Educational_Institute_of_Central_Greece"}
